profile_positions.description:
Baseline objective:
Creating winning upsell proposals aiming at satisfied customers and profitable contracts. 

Responsibility:
Responding to a clean upsell request the bid consultant is responsible for creating a publishable proposal that is:
-	Meeting the expectations of the customer (content, process, format);
-	Delivery committed;
-	Account Service Team reviewed;
-	Authorized according to organizational standards & processes;
-	In line with Account Service Team arrangements & expectations;
-	In line with Bid Factory KPI targets (hit rate, win rate, turnaround times, CSAT).

Role:
The bid consultant combines in one person the bidding roles:  Bid management, Solution management, Financial engineer and Proposal writer. The bid consultant has fit to purpose proficiency of these roles, making him/her a specialist for upsell proposals, not to mistake with colleagues specialized in bigger and/or complex deals.
